    "description": "The strategy is a single-asset, daily momentum-rotation system that seeks to concentrate exposure in the strongest risk-adjusted trending ETF from a predefined opportunity set dominated by leveraged sector and index products. Each day it ranks candidates using a composite momentum signal built from short, medium, and intermediate rate-of-change horizons, scaled by recent realized volatility to favor smoother trends. The score is further conditioned by a medium-term trend filter (price above a 50-day average gets full credit, otherwise discounted) and a modest RSI-based penalty intended to avoid extreme overbought or oversold conditions. The portfolio typically holds one ETF at a time, rotating only when the top-ranked asset exceeds the current holding by a material margin, and otherwise shifting to cash-like exposure when momentum deteriorates.",
